  the  biggest  ever  economic  reform  after independence  is  coming  through  the  amendment  to  the  central  goods  and service  tax  bill  in  the  country  with  the  introduction  of  goods  and  service tax  the  prices  of  the  items  will  be  reduced  and  the  tax  rates  may  also  come downwards  in  days  to  come  thereby  benefitting  the  common  man  directly  in the field of construction the tax rates are likely to come down from 30 percent to  18  or  20  percent  it  will  boost  the  foreign  and  domestic  investment  in  the country  through  this  bill  efforts  have  been  made  to  remove  the  hurdles coming in way of progressing industrialization and development of the country moreover  this  bill  will  help  in  strengthening  the  basic  condition  of  backward districts of the country  